1. The package name
2. Comments shouldn't exist, just TODO ones
3. Indentation is important
4. Naming conventions should be followed
5. The ode should fit in the standard 14 inch laptop screen.
6. Group similar values under an enumeration (enum).
7. Use a space ( ) between operators and operands.
8. Function arguments are separated by a , (comma) and a space
9. Use conditional operator for simple if structures
10. Code blocks start with { and ends with } even if they have a single instruction.
11.Define each variable on a single line.
12. Write the block closing bracket } on a single line. Except for if-else or try-catch.
13. Get rid of unused attributes
14. Avoid duplication of code
15. Use enums instead of constants